{"badges":["TM5","TM6"],"preparations":[{"content":["Preheat oven to 170°C. Line 2 baking trays (30 x 40 cm) with baking paper and set aside.","Place chocolate into mixing bowl and chop <nobr>5 sec\/speed 6<\/nobr> or until broken into small pieces. Transfer into a bowl and set aside.","Place oats into mixing bowl and chop <nobr>5 sec\/speed 5<\/nobr>. Transfer into a separate bowl and set aside.","Place brown sugar and caster sugar into mixing bowl and mill <nobr>40 sec\/speed 9<\/nobr>.","Add butter and mix <nobr>5 sec\/speed 8<\/nobr>."," <strong>Insert butterfly whisk<\/strong>. Whip <nobr>1 min\/speed 4<\/nobr>.","Scrape down sides of mixing bowl with spatula and whip <nobr>1 min\/speed 4<\/nobr> or until mixture is smooth. <strong>Remove butterfly whisk<\/strong>.","Add egg and vanilla and mix <nobr>15 sec\/speed 4<\/nobr>. Scrape down sides of mixing bowl with spatula.","Add flour and knead <nobr>20 sec\/<\/nobr>. Scrape down sides of mixing bowl with spatula.","Add baking powder, bicarbonate of soda, salt and reserved oats and knead <nobr>30 sec\/<\/nobr>, until well combined.","Transfer dough mixture into a large bowl and add pomegranate and reserved chocolate pieces. Gently stir to combine.","Place heaped tablespoons of mixture (approx. 24) onto reserved baking trays, approx. 5 cm apart. Bake for 15-17 minutes (170°C) or until golden brown.","Allow biscuits to cool on trays for 5 minutes, then transfer onto a wire rack to cool completely before serving."]}],"ingredients":[{"title":"","content":["80 g dark chocolate, broken into pieces (see Tips)","90 g rolled oats","90 g brown sugar","100 g caster sugar","125 g unsalted butter, softened","1 egg","1 tsp natural vanilla extract","200 g plain flour","½ tsp baking powder","½ tsp bicarbonate of soda","¼ tsp salt","1 pomegranate, arils removed"]}],"id":"r109103","imageLink":"https:\/\/4.bp.blogspot.com\/-LNiX_ApeXcQ\/XZWqxmmWgKI\/AAAAAAAAfdI\/erqQv77yDGwSiTVvJw8TUIOLBGv76vk2QCLcBGAsYHQ\/s1600\/0_UTDAja9JN40EfaMQ.png","title":"Choc chunk and pomegranate oatmeal cookies","publishedAt":"2017-03-19T00:00:00Z","nutrition":{"protein":"2.2 g","fat":"6.3 g","uom":"per 1 portion","carbohydrates":"18.8 g","calories":"593 kJ \/ 141 kcal"},"usefulItems":"small bowl , 2 baking trays (30 x 40 cm), baking paper, wire rack, large bowl, oven","hintsAndTricks":["This recipe was contributed by Amy Gordon."],"basicInfo":["easy","25m","45m","24 portions"]}